1
00:00:10,600 --> 00:00:12,633
<i>There's someone we didn't
do a background check.</i>

2
00:00:12,767 --> 00:00:14,533
<i>Him. Can we ask for a copy
of this?</i>

3
00:00:14,667 --> 00:00:16,133
<i> Why, Sir? Do you know him?</i>

4
00:00:16,267 --> 00:00:17,233
<i> He looks familiar.</i>

5
00:00:17,367 --> 00:00:20,333
<i>They say there was a big road
development</i>

6
00:00:20,467 --> 00:00:21,400
<i> project here 3 years ago.</i>

7
00:00:21,533 --> 00:00:23,433
<i>Where is the road
you're talking about?</i>

8
00:00:23,567 --> 00:00:25,867
<i>This is it, right here,
the one we're standing on.</i>

9
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:27,267
<i> My husband is so kind.</i>

10
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:30,600
<i> My husband! Tootsie!</i>

11
00:00:30,733 --> 00:00:33,467
<i>I won't let you insult me
in front of Tootsie!</i>

12
00:00:34,933 --> 00:00:37,900
<i>- Oh my god!
- Don't fight here!</i>

13
00:00:38,033 --> 00:00:39,833
<i> You both love him, right?</i>

14
00:00:39,967 --> 00:00:41,233
<i> Sorry!</i>

15
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:45,433
<i>I saw a rainbow.
I also saw a street sign.</i>

16
00:00:45,567 --> 00:00:46,867
<i> Raf. Saraf!</i>

17
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:48,100
<i> I, Glen Guerrero,</i>

18
00:00:48,233 --> 00:00:50,833
<i>succeed in the position of mayor
of Calabari City.</i>

19
00:00:50,967 --> 00:00:52,133
<i> Congratulations again.</i>

20
00:00:52,267 --> 00:00:53,167
<i> Mayor, congratulations.</i>

21
00:00:53,300 --> 00:00:54,500
<i>- Vince.
- He's the one</i>

22
00:00:54,633 --> 00:00:56,300
<i> I told you about my plus one.</i>

23
00:00:57,400 --> 00:00:59,100
<i>Wait. Did he do something wrong?</i>

24
00:00:59,233 --> 00:01:00,133
<i> What do you mean?</i>

25
00:01:00,267 --> 00:01:02,633
<i>We found out that Tootsie
is a cheater.</i>

26
00:01:02,767 --> 00:01:04,167
<i> And this is Zondra,</i>

27
00:01:04,300 --> 00:01:06,000
<i>she's been hurting her daughter,
Marie.</i>

28
00:01:06,133 --> 00:01:08,433
<i>It's the same way the victims
were killed.</i>

29
00:01:08,600 --> 00:01:09,700
<i>The weapon used was an icepick.</i>

30
00:01:09,833 --> 00:01:12,067
<i>It's possible that the killer
in the cold cases...</i>

31
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:14,833
<i>He also killed Zondra
and Tootsie?</i>

32
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:19,633
Whatever support Joaquin
got from us,

33
00:01:19,767 --> 00:01:22,567
I'll make sure to give you
the same support, Mayor.

34
00:01:23,600 --> 00:01:26,733
I'm all for the cleanliness
of Calabari.

35
00:01:28,033 --> 00:01:29,533
What I'm wearing here
is embarrassing.

36
00:01:31,067 --> 00:01:34,900
It doesn't suit me.
I just borrowed it from Allan.

37
00:01:35,233 --> 00:01:36,500
What's with you?

38
00:01:36,633 --> 00:01:38,867
You're wearing
a really nice outfit.

39
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:42,033
Besides, if you hadn't told me
you borrowed it from Allan,

40
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,767
I wouldn't have noticed.

41
00:01:44,267 --> 00:01:46,400
- Really?
- Yes!

42
00:01:46,533 --> 00:01:49,667
Besides, Vince,
no matter what you wear,

43
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:51,567
I'm sure I'll like it.

44
00:01:57,833 --> 00:01:59,833
You don't seem happy.

45
00:02:00,300 --> 00:02:01,767
What are you thinking about?

46
00:02:03,100 --> 00:02:05,233
Your brother doesn't seem
to like me.

47
00:02:06,700 --> 00:02:07,933
No.

48
00:02:08,067 --> 00:02:10,367
And besides,
you know each other already.

49
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:13,833
We were together when we saved
Grandmother Isang, right?

50
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,933
I'm sure my brother likes you.

51
00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:18,933
Of course, Faye,
that's different.

52
00:02:19,267 --> 00:02:21,167
I wasn't courting you
at that time,

53
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:23,567
but now, I'm courting you.

54
00:02:23,700 --> 00:02:24,567
You're something else.

55
00:02:24,700 --> 00:02:26,267
You're thinking about
a lot of things.

56
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:32,900
Don't think about it anymore.

57
00:02:33,033 --> 00:02:34,933
My brother is scared of me.

58
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:38,567
Just relax.

59
00:02:38,700 --> 00:02:39,667
Just eat.

60
00:02:41,667 --> 00:02:42,867
If you'll excuse us.

61
00:02:48,667 --> 00:02:49,767
Mayor!

62
00:02:49,900 --> 00:02:50,933
Good evening.

63
00:02:51,067 --> 00:02:52,300
Can I interview you,

64
00:02:52,433 --> 00:02:53,633
even if it's just
for a short time?

65
00:02:55,067 --> 00:02:57,833
Mira, can we find
some other time to do this?

66
00:02:57,967 --> 00:02:59,600
I'm pretty busy right now.

67
00:02:59,733 --> 00:03:02,867
It's about your road project
in Sitio Manggahan, Mayor.

68
00:03:37,867 --> 00:03:38,667
What about it, Mira?

69
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:40,867
How can I help you?

70
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:43,833
I'm following up on a story
about the road project

71
00:03:43,967 --> 00:03:46,333
that got me to Sitio Manggahan.

72
00:03:46,467 --> 00:03:47,633
Do you remember this?

73
00:03:48,767 --> 00:03:49,767
Yes, of course.

74
00:03:49,900 --> 00:03:51,667
That was my project
when I was still a councilor.

75
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:57,433
Based on the records
I looked at,

76
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:59,100
supposedly, the project
was supposed to be finished

77
00:03:59,233 --> 00:04:01,200
last year.

78
00:04:02,533 --> 00:04:04,667
Okay, so what's our problem
with that?

79
00:04:05,733 --> 00:04:08,133
There's no road at the site.

80
00:04:08,267 --> 00:04:13,667
The locals say the construction
never got underway.

81
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:15,433
It's a ghost project.

82
00:04:20,333 --> 00:04:22,133
Are you serious about this,
Mira?

83
00:04:22,267 --> 00:04:25,567
I need to know
because this is public money.

84
00:04:25,700 --> 00:04:28,167
Yes, I have proof, Mayor.
Here it is.

85
00:04:30,567 --> 00:04:32,100
What do you have to say
about that?

86
00:04:32,233 --> 00:04:34,000
This is unacceptable.

87
00:04:34,133 --> 00:04:35,500
I'm glad you brought it up.

88
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:41,333
Well, I just want to get your
side of the story

89
00:04:41,467 --> 00:04:43,833
before I pass it on
to my editor-in-chief.

90
00:04:46,367 --> 00:04:49,100
Well, Mira,
that's good journalism,

91
00:04:49,233 --> 00:04:50,800
but I'm sorry.

92
00:04:50,933 --> 00:04:53,600
When it comes to the budget,
I only approve of it.

93
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:55,800
But when it comes to
construction,

94
00:04:55,933 --> 00:04:57,633
I'm not part of it.

95
00:04:57,767 --> 00:04:59,233
But don't worry.

96
00:04:59,367 --> 00:05:00,867
I'll get to the bottom of it.

97
00:05:03,867 --> 00:05:05,400
And someone has to pay.

98
00:05:12,267 --> 00:05:14,167
- Bautista?
- Yes, Sir?

99
00:05:14,300 --> 00:05:19,200
Do you remember Monty,
the pimple patch pusher?

100
00:05:19,333 --> 00:05:20,467
Yes, Sir.

101
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:23,700
Actually, Torres, De Jesus,
and I tried to track him down,

102
00:05:23,833 --> 00:05:26,133
but we reached a dead end.

103
00:05:26,267 --> 00:05:27,367
Why, Sir?

104
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:29,700
What connection does he have
with Mando's escape?

105
00:05:31,467 --> 00:05:32,467
Here.

106
00:05:35,767 --> 00:05:39,333
This is the CCTV footage
here at our place.

107
00:05:39,467 --> 00:05:41,467
This is the connection
I'm looking for.

108
00:05:44,567 --> 00:05:46,300
He also visited Monty!

109
00:05:46,433 --> 00:05:49,000
Yes, that's why Chief needs
to know this.

110
00:05:50,767 --> 00:05:53,933
But why did you come straight
to me, not to Chief?

111
00:05:58,333 --> 00:06:00,433
Lesson!
I'm teaching you a lesson!

112
00:06:00,567 --> 00:06:01,767
Don't ask too many questions.

113
00:06:01,900 --> 00:06:03,033
Come on, come on.

114
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:07,133
What's with you?

115
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:08,333
Just mind the yellow ones.

116
00:06:09,633 --> 00:06:10,800
Boss!

117
00:06:11,067 --> 00:06:13,100
We've collected a lot today.

118
00:06:13,233 --> 00:06:14,233
It looks like we can make up

119
00:06:14,367 --> 00:06:16,200
for the loss
of the pimple patch.

120
00:06:16,533 --> 00:06:18,533
You know, you never learn.

121
00:06:18,667 --> 00:06:21,467
You're still reminding the Mayor
of your blunder.

122
00:06:23,933 --> 00:06:25,767
Boss, I'm sorry.

123
00:06:25,900 --> 00:06:30,367
By the way, what's your plan
for that reporter?

124
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:35,967
If I, if I can have it my way,
I won't let it drag on.

125
00:06:36,100 --> 00:06:37,967
The mess is getting bigger.

126
00:06:38,100 --> 00:06:39,900
You're mayor now,
maybe it'll come back to you.

127
00:06:40,033 --> 00:06:42,667
Her editor-in-chief knows
about this issue.

128
00:06:42,833 --> 00:06:47,567
It's in the public records,
and my name is on the project.

129
00:06:48,733 --> 00:06:50,167
If something happens to Mira,

130
00:06:51,433 --> 00:06:53,333
it's like I'm saying I'm guilty.

131
00:06:55,700 --> 00:06:56,967
So what's the plan, Mayor?

132
00:07:05,333 --> 00:07:06,167
Come in!

133
00:07:09,100 --> 00:07:10,367
Sir.

134
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:11,967
- Sir.
- Garcia.

135
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:14,933
Can we bother you?

136
00:07:16,133 --> 00:07:17,767
What's that again, Garcia?

137
00:07:17,900 --> 00:07:19,567
How's your assignment
with Bautista?

138
00:07:20,933 --> 00:07:23,100
Sir, we have something
to show you.

139
00:07:25,367 --> 00:07:26,600
Sir,

140
00:07:26,733 --> 00:07:30,300
that's the person who last
visited Mando

141
00:07:30,433 --> 00:07:31,833
before he escaped.

142
00:07:32,867 --> 00:07:33,867
And then?

143
00:07:35,933 --> 00:07:37,033
Here.

144
00:07:38,100 --> 00:07:43,033
It's the same guy who visited
Monty before Monty escaped.

145
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:52,033
This guy is connected to Monty
and Mando's escape.

146
00:07:52,533 --> 00:07:54,000
Has this guy been identified?

147
00:07:54,133 --> 00:07:55,267
Not yet, Sir.

148
00:07:55,400 --> 00:07:58,033
He wrote an alias
in the visitor's logbook.

149
00:07:58,167 --> 00:08:02,467
Sir, we need to catch
that guy so we can find out

150
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:05,633
who really let Monty
and Mando escape.

151
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:08,800
Okay.

152
00:08:08,933 --> 00:08:10,067
Work on that.

153
00:08:11,467 --> 00:08:14,167
Good job, Garcia, Bautista.

154
00:08:14,300 --> 00:08:17,033
- Thank you, Sir, as always.
- Thank you, Sir.

155
00:08:17,167 --> 00:08:18,033
Did you hear that?

156
00:08:18,167 --> 00:08:20,000
You're even credited
because of my good work.

157
00:08:24,033 --> 00:08:25,400
Mar...

158
00:08:25,533 --> 00:08:27,267
You're so quiet.

159
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:28,433
What happened to you?

160
00:08:30,667 --> 00:08:32,667
When I'm loud, you get annoyed.

161
00:08:32,967 --> 00:08:34,900
When I'm quiet,
you ask questions.

162
00:08:35,033 --> 00:08:36,867
What do you really want, Abdul?

163
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,100
You're overreacting.

164
00:08:38,233 --> 00:08:39,667
I'm only checking on you.

165
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:41,233
I've been thinking, you know.

166
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:44,233
Don't we have a lot of friends
who are gay?

167
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,800
It seems like we need
to check on them.

168
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:50,467
Do you miss them?

169
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:51,733
No!

170
00:08:52,167 --> 00:08:56,100
I just want to warn them
about this serial killer.

171
00:08:56,467 --> 00:08:59,633
Who knows, they can give you
information

172
00:08:59,767 --> 00:09:02,967
that will help catch
this gay killer, right?

173
00:09:18,433 --> 00:09:19,300
<i> Where do you want to eat?</i>

174
00:09:19,433 --> 00:09:23,533
<i>- It's up to you.
- Okay, okay.</i>

175
00:09:25,033 --> 00:09:26,367
<i> I'm hungry.</i>

176
00:09:27,667 --> 00:09:30,733
<i>I'll just accept your decision
to reject me.</i>

177
00:09:30,867 --> 00:09:32,033
<i> It's not like that!</i>

178
00:09:32,167 --> 00:09:35,567
<i>All I'm saying is,
let's take it easy.</i>

179
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:37,067
<i> Tonyo, do you want chicken?</i>

180
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:37,967
<i> No, I'm good.</i>

181
00:09:38,100 --> 00:09:39,233
<i> Okay.</i>

182
00:09:41,333 --> 00:09:42,833
<i> Let's eat.</i>

183
00:09:43,133 --> 00:09:44,200
<i> You'll just eat salad?</i>

184
00:09:56,167 --> 00:10:00,267
<i>Sometimes, we don't need sermons
and worries.</i>

185
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:04,000
<i>Sometimes, we just need an ally.</i>

186
00:10:30,900 --> 00:10:33,067
Bobby, be strong.

187
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:36,200
Don't be weak.

188
00:10:36,333 --> 00:10:38,100
He betrayed you.

189
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:44,767
Let him go crazy!

190
00:10:48,700 --> 00:10:56,533
But he'll go crazy
if I answer this,

191
00:10:56,667 --> 00:10:58,433
and then I won't talk.

192
00:11:06,900 --> 00:11:08,167
It got cut off.

193
00:11:09,533 --> 00:11:10,533
You're lucky!

194
00:11:26,300 --> 00:11:27,667
Noble,

195
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:29,000
if Chief comes looking for me,

196
00:11:29,133 --> 00:11:30,700
tell him I just dropped by
somewhere.

197
00:11:30,833 --> 00:11:32,533
Where are you going, Ma'am?

198
00:11:32,667 --> 00:11:34,233
It's better if you don't know.

199
00:11:35,367 --> 00:11:36,900
I don't like the sound of that,
Ma'am...

200
00:11:37,033 --> 00:11:39,233
Maybe later you'll do something
else that will make Chief

201
00:11:39,367 --> 00:11:40,433
even angrier with you.

202
00:11:40,567 --> 00:11:42,933
Noble, can you stop worrying
so much?

203
00:11:43,100 --> 00:11:44,167
Just think about it,

204
00:11:44,300 --> 00:11:47,000
I'm doing this because I want
to find the killer.

205
00:11:48,700 --> 00:11:49,700
Okay, okay.

206
00:11:49,833 --> 00:11:53,000
Just in case you need backup,
just call, Ma'am.

207
00:11:53,133 --> 00:11:54,667
Okay, Noble. Thank you.

208
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:55,767
Okay, Ma'am.

209
00:12:02,867 --> 00:12:03,933
Miss.

210
00:12:05,467 --> 00:12:07,367
Do you know a Mrs. Miranda?

211
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:08,467
Yes.

212
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:10,567
There she is.

213
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:13,333
- Okay, okay, thank you.
- Yes.

214
00:12:15,800 --> 00:12:18,300
Good day, Mrs. Miranda.

215
00:12:18,433 --> 00:12:20,200
I'm Sergeant Bobby Enriquez.

216
00:12:20,333 --> 00:12:21,933
What can I do for you?

217
00:12:22,067 --> 00:12:24,367
Is this about
my brother's killer?

218
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:26,333
Have you caught the killer yet?

219
00:12:26,467 --> 00:12:28,033
Not yet.

220
00:12:28,167 --> 00:12:30,167
But I'm here to ask you
something.

221
00:12:30,300 --> 00:12:32,000
Maybe you have some more
information

222
00:12:32,133 --> 00:12:34,667
that you can tell us
so that we can see that killer.

223
00:12:38,067 --> 00:12:40,533
Bok, how's that?

224
00:12:40,667 --> 00:12:42,933
Alma didn't even say
a date or day.

225
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,967
That's our situation, Bok.

226
00:12:46,100 --> 00:12:47,667
We need to solve

227
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:50,633
what these visions
are that are like puzzles.

228
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:52,133
That's a bit vague.

229
00:12:52,467 --> 00:12:54,300
How can we solve that?

230
00:12:54,767 --> 00:12:57,700
It's just the name
of the street, Saraf?

231
00:12:58,033 --> 00:12:59,667
And then the color
of the rainbow?

232
00:12:59,933 --> 00:13:01,000
Where are you going
to find that anyway?

233
00:13:01,133 --> 00:13:02,567
What does that mean?

234
00:13:05,133 --> 00:13:06,467
Let's go around.

235
00:13:09,500 --> 00:13:12,033
Ma'am, Sir, she's our manager.

236
00:13:12,167 --> 00:13:13,033
Thank you.

237
00:13:13,167 --> 00:13:14,967
Yes? How can I help you?

238
00:13:15,100 --> 00:13:16,367
Good day.

239
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:18,967
I'm Lieutenant Sandro Paloma,

240
00:13:19,100 --> 00:13:22,000
and this is my partner,
Lieutenant Charlie Samson.

241
00:13:22,367 --> 00:13:23,500
This is just a follow-up

242
00:13:23,633 --> 00:13:26,033
to the robbery of your hardware
two weeks ago.

243
00:13:26,167 --> 00:13:28,167
Has the robber been caught?

244
00:13:28,300 --> 00:13:29,200
No, not yet.

245
00:13:29,333 --> 00:13:31,400
So we'll go
through it all again,

246
00:13:31,533 --> 00:13:34,000
maybe we just missed
some details.

247
00:13:34,133 --> 00:13:35,300
What do you need?

248
00:13:35,433 --> 00:13:38,100
We need to review
the CCTV footage.

249
00:13:44,100 --> 00:13:46,433
It's been six years,

250
00:13:46,567 --> 00:13:48,900
and the suspect
is still missing.

251
00:13:49,033 --> 00:13:51,500
He was stabbed several times
with an ice pick.

252
00:13:51,633 --> 00:13:53,267
What's his crime?

253
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:54,767
That he turned out to be gay?

254
00:13:57,567 --> 00:14:00,033
That's what I'm working on now.

255
00:14:00,167 --> 00:14:03,100
There were two gay men
found dead.

256
00:14:03,233 --> 00:14:05,967
It's the same thing
with your brother,

257
00:14:06,100 --> 00:14:07,333
stabbed with an ice pick.

258
00:14:07,467 --> 00:14:09,033
Really?

259
00:14:09,167 --> 00:14:11,033
What can I help you with?

260
00:14:11,167 --> 00:14:13,600
When I told the police
who the suspect was,

261
00:14:13,733 --> 00:14:15,500
they didn't believe me.

262
00:14:15,633 --> 00:14:17,633
Do you have a suspect?

263
00:14:17,767 --> 00:14:18,800
Who is he?

264
00:14:19,967 --> 00:14:21,267
Where is he?

265
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:22,700
It's Matmat!

266
00:14:22,833 --> 00:14:24,833
But I don't know
where that person is anymore.

267
00:14:24,967 --> 00:14:27,100
Maybe his mother is hiding him.

268
00:14:27,233 --> 00:14:29,567
You can go to her house.

269
00:14:29,733 --> 00:14:32,533
Can you tell me
where I can find him?

270
00:14:32,667 --> 00:14:33,767
Yes.

271
00:14:36,333 --> 00:14:39,767
Wait. After the investigation,

272
00:14:39,900 --> 00:14:42,567
the new CCTV feed
was overridden.

273
00:14:42,700 --> 00:14:45,733
The footage of the robbery
is gone.

274
00:14:45,867 --> 00:14:47,333
So you don't have a copy?

275
00:14:47,467 --> 00:14:48,467
It's gone.

276
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:49,667
What's this?

277
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:51,267
Your store got robbed,

278
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:53,700
and then you suddenly deleted
your CCTV footage?

279
00:14:53,833 --> 00:14:55,767
Sorry. That's the mandate
from above

280
00:14:55,900 --> 00:14:57,733
so that we can be paid
by insurance.

281
00:14:57,867 --> 00:14:59,133
Since you've been paid,

282
00:14:59,267 --> 00:15:02,433
you don't care anymore whether
the thief was caught or not?

283
00:15:09,633 --> 00:15:10,600
Sorry.

284
00:15:13,967 --> 00:15:14,867
Excuse me, Miss.

285
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:16,933
I just wanted to ask a question.

286
00:15:17,067 --> 00:15:21,233
Do you know of a street here
called "Saraf"?

287
00:15:21,367 --> 00:15:22,233
Saraf?

288
00:15:22,367 --> 00:15:23,000
Saraf.

289
00:15:23,367 --> 00:15:27,100
- Oh, no, no. Nothing.
- Okay, thank you.

290
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:30,533
Come on, Bok, let's move
to another village.

291
00:15:30,667 --> 00:15:32,867
I just texted Alma,

292
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:35,400
but she said she didn't remember
any other details.

293
00:15:37,133 --> 00:15:38,533
How's that Bok?

294
00:15:38,667 --> 00:15:40,267
That's all we have.

295
00:15:41,933 --> 00:15:43,300
Bok, wait.

296
00:15:43,433 --> 00:15:46,467
I know her vision at the
Stiletto Comedy Bar was right,

297
00:15:47,533 --> 00:15:49,367
but...

298
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:51,167
something's bothering me.

299
00:15:52,700 --> 00:15:53,800
What if we're wrong?

300
00:15:54,833 --> 00:15:57,633
What if we're following
a different lead

301
00:15:57,767 --> 00:15:59,400
because we listened to Alma?

302
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:05,800
Bok, it's not that
I'm destroying your strategy,

303
00:16:05,933 --> 00:16:07,300
but I'm just being truthful.

304
00:16:14,100 --> 00:16:15,300
You're right, Bok.

305
00:16:17,067 --> 00:16:18,267
You have a point.

306
00:16:20,167 --> 00:16:21,333
But if it's just you,

307
00:16:22,467 --> 00:16:23,267
if it's just you,

308
00:16:24,500 --> 00:16:27,133
how are you going to find
that killer?

309
00:16:27,267 --> 00:16:30,100
Bok, you know, honestly,
if it's just me,

310
00:16:30,233 --> 00:16:33,733
I'll go back to the street
where you and Noble chased him.

311
00:16:33,867 --> 00:16:35,233
Who knows, there's CCTV there,

312
00:16:35,367 --> 00:16:36,767
the killer's face was captured.

313
00:16:38,167 --> 00:16:39,100
That's good, Bok.

314
00:16:40,300 --> 00:16:44,000
So okay, I'm going
to the next village.

315
00:16:44,167 --> 00:16:47,133
Follow up
on your investigation first.

316
00:16:47,267 --> 00:16:49,267
Wait, are you sure?

317
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:51,533
Maybe you'll say
I'm leaving you.

318
00:16:51,667 --> 00:16:53,633
No, that's okay.

319
00:16:53,767 --> 00:16:55,933
So we can cover a lot, too.

320
00:16:56,067 --> 00:16:57,533
Okay, it's up to you.

321
00:17:04,300 --> 00:17:05,267
Bok!

322
00:17:06,900 --> 00:17:07,900
Wait, Bok.

323
00:17:09,600 --> 00:17:10,267
Why?

324
00:17:11,367 --> 00:17:14,000
I think I know
how to solve that puzzle.

325
00:17:21,267 --> 00:17:22,267
Mira.

326
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:24,233
How's your assignment?

327
00:17:24,367 --> 00:17:26,100
That's what I came here for.

328
00:17:27,367 --> 00:17:29,267
Ma'am Bobby isn't here yet,
right?

329
00:17:29,400 --> 00:17:30,567
Not yet.

330
00:17:30,700 --> 00:17:31,767
Why?

331
00:17:32,833 --> 00:17:34,700
The road project
I'm investigating,

332
00:17:36,167 --> 00:17:37,900
Jake, is a ghost project.

333
00:17:38,033 --> 00:17:39,500
Ghost project?

334
00:17:39,633 --> 00:17:41,367
A project where funds
were released,

335
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:43,133
but it never got off the ground.

336
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:47,633
And do you know who handled
that project?

337
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:48,767
Who?

338
00:17:48,900 --> 00:17:50,033
Mayor Glen,

339
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:52,633
when he was a councilor.

340
00:17:52,767 --> 00:17:53,733
Mayor Glen?

341
00:17:55,533 --> 00:17:56,533
Mayor Glen?

342
00:17:56,667 --> 00:17:58,300
Actually, I've talked to him.

343
00:17:58,433 --> 00:18:00,567
He said he's only there
until the budget is approved.

344
00:18:00,700 --> 00:18:02,733
But he has no hand
in the construction.

345
00:18:02,867 --> 00:18:05,333
You don't believe him, do you?

346
00:18:05,467 --> 00:18:06,833
I don't know.

347
00:18:08,767 --> 00:18:10,233
But what I know is,

348
00:18:10,367 --> 00:18:12,733
I still have a lot to dig
into about this.

349
00:18:15,267 --> 00:18:16,467
Noble.

350
00:18:16,600 --> 00:18:18,167
- Sir?
- Have you seen Enriquez?

351
00:18:18,300 --> 00:18:20,033
She's on her way here.

352
00:18:20,167 --> 00:18:22,667
Tell her I want to talk to her.

353
00:18:22,833 --> 00:18:23,800
Okay, Sir.

354
00:18:25,067 --> 00:18:26,600
Sir...

355
00:18:26,733 --> 00:18:28,400
Can we ask a question?

356
00:18:28,533 --> 00:18:29,633
What's that, Noble?

357
00:18:29,767 --> 00:18:30,567
Sir,

358
00:18:30,700 --> 00:18:32,400
if we find out
about a ghost project

359
00:18:32,533 --> 00:18:36,733
and Mayor Glen is involved,
what can we do?

360
00:18:39,500 --> 00:18:42,400
Noble, that's not our job.

361
00:18:42,533 --> 00:18:44,233
That's under the Ombudsman.

362
00:18:44,367 --> 00:18:47,500
Unless there's a criminal case,
we can't do anything.

363
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:50,367
Copy, Chief.

364
00:19:02,100 --> 00:19:03,067
What, Mar?

365
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:05,167
Have you talked
to your frennies yet?

366
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:06,267
Yes.

367
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:10,133
Let's go to Freddy first,
the one with the salon.

368
00:19:10,267 --> 00:19:12,100
He's the closest one.

369
00:19:12,233 --> 00:19:13,467
Okay,

370
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:17,100
but I hope we don't
have to go there in vain,

371
00:19:17,233 --> 00:19:19,200
so our sweat won't be wasted.

372
00:19:19,333 --> 00:19:20,433
Girl, it's hot.

373
00:19:20,567 --> 00:19:22,167
My collagen is wasted.

374
00:19:22,300 --> 00:19:24,500
That's why I brought
an umbrella, right?

375
00:19:24,633 --> 00:19:26,533
He is ready!

376
00:19:26,667 --> 00:19:28,500
- Let's go.
- Okay, okay.

377
00:19:28,667 --> 00:19:29,900
He's all set.

378
00:19:30,033 --> 00:19:31,033
- Yes.
- Why are you the only one

379
00:19:31,167 --> 00:19:31,933
with an umbrella?

380
00:19:32,067 --> 00:19:33,133
Did you see that, Bok?

381
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:36,867
That's Santa Ramona Street.

382
00:19:37,967 --> 00:19:40,433
But because of the vandal,

383
00:19:40,567 --> 00:19:42,300
Taram is the only one reading.

384
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:46,067
Saraf...

385
00:19:47,433 --> 00:19:49,733
Where can we find that street?

386
00:19:49,867 --> 00:19:51,767
It's impossible in San Rafael.

387
00:19:54,133 --> 00:19:55,967
All I know is,

388
00:19:56,100 --> 00:20:00,033
there's Casa Rafael Avenue
south of Calabari.

389
00:20:00,167 --> 00:20:01,200
Right, right.

390
00:20:01,333 --> 00:20:02,400
I know that street.

391
00:20:02,567 --> 00:20:04,467
I passed by it while I was
patrolling the streets.

392
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:07,067
Okay, I'll go there.

393
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:09,500
And you continue
your investigation here.

394
00:20:09,867 --> 00:20:11,633
Bok, really now?

395
00:20:11,767 --> 00:20:13,400
Of course, I'll come with you.

396
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:17,067
- What, let's go?
- Let's go.

397
00:20:21,800 --> 00:20:22,767
Driver, we'll get off here.

398
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:25,567
Thank you!

399
00:20:25,700 --> 00:20:28,567
- Here's our payment!
- Thank you!

400
00:20:31,933 --> 00:20:33,833
Mar, come here.

401
00:20:34,967 --> 00:20:37,600
Are you sure we got off
at the right place?

402
00:20:37,933 --> 00:20:40,400
It doesn't look like
Freddy's salon is here.

403
00:20:40,533 --> 00:20:42,300
All I know is, it's on Estrada.

404
00:20:42,433 --> 00:20:44,533
He moved years ago.

405
00:20:44,667 --> 00:20:46,833
Well, that place is flooded.

406
00:20:46,967 --> 00:20:51,400
And I think
that's the correct street.

407
00:20:51,533 --> 00:20:54,200
What are you waiting for?
Let's go!

408
00:20:54,333 --> 00:20:56,333
He's so fussy.

409
00:20:56,467 --> 00:20:58,267
Is that how you point out
a street?

410
00:20:58,400 --> 00:21:00,267
Hurry up.
You might get run over there.

411
00:21:08,967 --> 00:21:10,233
Oh, babe.

412
00:21:10,367 --> 00:21:12,700
Sorry, I just answered
your call.

413
00:21:13,233 --> 00:21:16,200
Yes, I got busy.

414
00:21:16,333 --> 00:21:19,600
And of course, yes,
I will pay my 100k debt.

415
00:21:19,733 --> 00:21:21,667
My bills piled up,

416
00:21:21,800 --> 00:21:23,533
it's like they're racing
to the finish line.

417
00:21:24,667 --> 00:21:26,867
Yes, send me your account now.

418
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:29,033
I'll pay you after this call.

419
00:21:29,167 --> 00:21:30,067
Okay?

420
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:32,367
Okay, bye!

421
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:34,300
Pay your face.

422
00:21:34,433 --> 00:21:37,133
Goodbye, 100k.

423
00:21:39,433 --> 00:21:40,667
You're blocked now.

424
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:43,833
Miss, what now?

425
00:21:43,967 --> 00:21:46,167
<i>Come on. I'm just waiting
for you, Madam.</i>

426
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:07,700
What's your plan, Mayor?

427
00:22:07,833 --> 00:22:10,533
Boss, do you want me
to kill that reporter?

428
00:22:10,667 --> 00:22:14,000
Based on our police officer
friend, there's a pattern.

429
00:22:14,133 --> 00:22:15,267
What pattern? What is this?
Bingo?

430
00:22:15,433 --> 00:22:19,067
The killer is targeting either
a cheater,

431
00:22:19,200 --> 00:22:20,300
an abusive parent,

432
00:22:20,433 --> 00:22:21,833
or a scammer.

433
00:22:21,967 --> 00:22:22,967
Hello, Sir Tonyo?

434
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:24,667
Yes, we've figured out
the street.

435
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:26,667
We're here now
at Casa Rafael Avenue.

436
00:22:26,800 --> 00:22:28,433
Sir, that's what
I'm calling you for.

437
00:22:28,567 --> 00:22:29,867
My vision has cleared up.

438
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:32,000
The Rainbow design
I was telling you about,

439
00:22:32,133 --> 00:22:33,733
- it's on an umbrella!
- Umbrella?

440
00:22:33,867 --> 00:22:35,133
I saw a birthmark.

441
00:22:35,267 --> 00:22:37,233
The killer has a birthmark
on his hand!

442
00:22:37,367 --> 00:22:38,400
Birthmark...
